## Quality bar — self-check before showing the draft

- [ ] Audience mode is correctly identified and length matches the table.
- [ ] First sentence states the outcome, decision, or ask.
- [ ] At least one KPI or compliance reference is present (or explicitly noted as N/A).
- [ ] Specific names instead of "the team" wherever a person did the work.
- [ ] No fabricated numbers, quotes, or attributions.
- [ ] Three subject/opener options offered.
- [ ] Recipients resolved with people search; draft stops at Scout's confirmation step, never auto-sent.
- [ ] No labeled/Confidential content pasted into an unprotected draft or channel.
- [ ] Risks/sensitivities section completed (write "none identified" if none).

If any check fails, revise before showing the draft.
